Health Minister Zweli Mkhize says the country has managed to avoid the spread of imported COVID-19 cases. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize says the country has managed to avoid the spread of imported COVID-19 cases. He's used a graph to demonstrate the trend witnessed in many countries across the globe. Mkhize says the lockdown helped stop new infections which could have been carried by people coming from outside the country. WATCH: Masks can protect against COVID-19 He said there are now 13,488 tracers involved. The minister says going forward, people may be required to wear masks in overcrowded places. The number of COVID-19 related deaths in South Africa has risen to 24. The number of confirmed coronavirus cases in South Africa is 2,003. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.